This code implements a simple URL shortener with a basic HTTP server in Python. The server has two main functionalities: it shortens URLs when accessed at `/shorten?url=<original_url>` and it redirects shortened URLs to their original destinations. The short URL is a random 6-character string generated from letters and digits, stored in an in-memory dictionary. The server listens on port 8080 and is designed to run indefinitely.

